A Concurrent Resolution recognizing National Lineman
Appreciation Day; praising lineworkers from Oklahoma
electric providers; and celebrating their work to
power homes and businesses across the state.
WHEREAS, as the true heroes of the electric power industry,
lineworkers are responsible for maintaining and repairing electrical
power grids 24 hours a day, 365 days a year; and
WHEREAS, these dedicated professionals are often the first to
respond during storms and other catastrophic weather events so other
first responders can get to the scene safely; and
WHEREAS, lineworkers operate under dangerous conditions and risk
their lives high atop power lines to keep electricity flowing; and
WHEREAS, lineworkers also play a vital role in Oklahomaâ€™s
economy by maintaining the energy infrastructure that powers homes
and businesses; and
WHEREAS, lineworkers deserve recognition for their hard work to
power local communities and keep people safe during emergencies.
NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE 1ST SESSION
OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
CONCURRING THEREIN:
THAT the Oklahoma Legislature recognizes April 18, 2025, as
National Lineman Appreciation Day.

THAT the Oklahoma Legislature extends its gratitude to
lineworkers from Public Service Company of Oklahoma, Oklahoma Gas
and Electric Company, Oklahoma Municipal Power Authority, the Grand
River Dam Authority, local electric cooperatives, and all other
electric providers for their dedicated service and swift action to
restore power in emergency situations.
THAT the Oklahoma Legislature commends lineworkers for their
vital role in powering homes and businesses throughout the state.
THAT the Oklahoma Legislature honors lineworkers for their
critical service in all types of weather, recognizing them as
essential first responders who risk their lives to ensure the safety
and well-being of all communities.
Adopted by the Senate the 17th day of April, 2025.
